title: About Me
description_1: Senior Data Scientist / Statistical Programmer with 6+ years of experience building production-grade R packages, automated clinical trial pipelines, and reproducible TFL workflows in regulated environments. Deep expertise in R, CDISC standards (SDTM/ADaM), statistical programming, and end-to-end automation across large-scale clinical datasets. Proven track record of saving thousands of analyst hours through tooling, package development, and workflow optimization.

title: Senior Data Scientist
description_1: Authored and maintained multiple production R packages used company-wide for clinical trial analysis, validation, and reporting.
description_2: Built automated R Markdown pipelines generating hundreds of Tables, Figures, and Listings (TFLs) to support trial accuracy assessments and regulatory reporting.
description_3: Developed and documented derived variables under CDISC standards (SDTM, ADaM, CDASH) with Git/GitLab collaboration and AWS S3 data management.
description_4: Created an R Shiny app to visualize cancer screening timelines and key events leading to diagnosis.
description_5: Provided statistical programming support for data cleaning, database locks, SAP-driven analyses, and exploratory investigations.
description_6: Partnered with biostatisticians to translate SAPs into analysis specifications and reusable code.
description_7: Built reproducible pipelines with unit tests and a shared code library to ensure audit-ready, backward-compatible outputs.

title: Reporting Analyst
description_1: Automated weekly accounts receivable aging report in R with HTML/CSS email delivery, saving ~5 hours per week.
description_2: Built ad hoc dashboards and data visualizations to support leadership requests.
description_3: Served as analytics liaison across teams to align reporting needs and delivery.
description_4: Automated batch invoice emails and Azure Web App exports, reducing manual effort across teams.

title: Actuarial Analyst
description_1: Automated CRG band renewal in R, reducing runtime from 8 hours to under 1 minute.
description_2: Automated demographic and plan risk factor workflows and forecasting models with Excel/R integration.
description_3: Automated CRG proposal and mental health parity processes; documented methods and led stakeholder walkthroughs.
description_4: Fit empirical distributions using KS tests and MLE for actuarial modeling.
